''Inflammatory heart disease'' involves inflammation of the heart muscle and/or the tissue surrounding it.
* [[Endocarditis]] – [[inflammation]] of the inner layer of the [[heart]], the [[endocardium]]. The most common structures involved are the [[heart valve]]s.
* [[Inflammation|Inflammatory]] [[cardiomegaly]]
* [[Myocarditis]] – [[inflammation]] of the [[myocardium]], the muscular part of the heart.

===د زړه د والونو ناروغۍ===
{{main|Valvular heart disease}}

''Valvular heart disease'' is  disease process that affects one or more [[Heart valve|valves]] of the [[heart]]. There are four major heart valve which may be affected by valvular heart disease, including the [[tricuspid valve|tricuspid]] and [[aortic valve|aortic valves]] in the right side of the heart, as well as the [[mitral valve|mitral]] and [[aortic valve|aortic valves]] in the left side of the heart.

